<L>__{interior dusk. thornfield the red room.}
<A>__{jane, aged ten, is walking along the long gallery. she opens a door and finds herself in the red room. she stares into the mirror, searching the pale face of her reflection, as if trying to find an answer. a murmur seems to come down the gaping chimney; a woman's deep sigh. jane's throat tightens with fear. something moves in the shadows behind her. she scans them, her eyes full of terror. jane knows beyond all doubt that something is there. she hears a low laugh. it seems to be right next to her. she tries to scream }
